Q2. Battery-powered design: a camera needs 5V regulated. Battery is a 3.7V Li-ion, nominal 3.7V, range 3.0V to 4.2V (discharged to charged).
(a) At V_in=3.0V: find D for |V_out|=5V. Is this step-up?
(b) At V_in=4.2V: find D for |V_out|=5V. Is this step-up or step-down?
(c) At V_in=5.0V: what is D? What does this operating point represent?
(d) Find the range of switch voltage stress across the battery discharge cycle
(e) What minimum MOSFET voltage rating is needed (use 20% derating at the worst case)?
